[normal] A study of the Irish system for which the system operator publishes the CO2 emissions every 15 minutes found that when the pumped storage system was being refurbished and the balancing of the variability of the wind was undertaken by CCGTs the effectiveness of CO2 mitigation plummeted; with 12% wind production the mitigation was only 4%.  The reason is that cycling the CCGTs reduces their thermal efficiency and so increases their CO2 emissions, see “Wind – 
[normal]Whitehall
[normal]’s pointless profligacy
